{"key":"processedPost-8645405","value":{"id":8645405,"first":8597867,"last":8648206,"when":1216276377,"utime":"07/17/08 09:32 AM","content":"Grains should never be added to boiling water.&nbsp; That's a major cause of burst kernels.&nbsp; At the very least, add the grains to cold water and then bring to a boil.<br /><br />Hot water hydrates the grains much faster, so if you dump dry grains into boiling water, how can they absorb that much water without bursting?&nbsp; The soak allows them to slowly absorb water, eliminating that problem.<br /><br />Some growers are satisfied with ten percent burst kernels.&nbsp; Personally, if I saw ten TOTAL burst kernels, I'd toss the whole batch and start over. Loose starch in jars is never a good thing.<br />RR","title":"Re: No-Soak WBS prep, and you... a side by side study.. hehe"}}